HEADWORD: Collative
<hw>Col*la"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>collativus</ets> brought together. ]</ety> <def>Passing or held by
collation; -- said of livings of which the bishop and the patron are the
same person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

